# Cognee configuration — copy to `.env` in the process/dir where Cognee runs (the memory page only).
# Ollama is a global system service; models live in ~/.ollama (NOT in this repo).
# Verified installed on this machine: glm-4.7-flash:latest (LLM) + nomic-embed-text:latest (embeddings).

# --- Cognee's LLM: graph extraction (cognify) + distillation (curator/writer) → local Ollama / GLM ---
LLM_PROVIDER="ollama"
LLM_MODEL="glm-4.7-flash:latest"
LLM_ENDPOINT="http://localhost:11434/v1"     # note the /v1
LLM_API_KEY="ollama"                         # dummy value, but must be non-empty

# --- Cognee's embeddings (recall / vector search) → local Ollama / nomic-embed-text ---
EMBEDDING_PROVIDER="ollama"
EMBEDDING_MODEL="nomic-embed-text"
EMBEDDING_ENDPOINT="http://localhost:11434/api/embeddings"
EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS=768                      # must match nomic-embed-text

# If Cognee runs inside Docker, replace localhost with host.docker.internal in both endpoints.
#
# Install Cognee pinned to a commit that PROVABLY contains PR #3107
# ("session: session semantic retrieval distillation" — session_id memory,
#  add_feedback / get_session / distill_session). Pin = the #3107 squash-merge:
#   pip install "git+https://github.com/topoteretes/cognee.git@ba35b2fd34f16040e7e95aa4a3377eca1a18b1bf"
#
# Pin provenance (verified 2026-06-20 against the live install):
#   - PR #3107 merged to `dev` as ba35b2fd34f16040e7e95aa4a3377eca1a18b1bf
#     (git describe: v1.2.0.dev1-44-gba35b2fd). It IS the merge commit, so it
#     definitionally contains #3107, and it is a descendant of the previously
#     documented c505f326 (v1.2.0.dev1-37) — nothing is lost.
#   - The live venv at /tmp/cognee_smoke/venv reports cognee 1.2.0.dev1 and the
#     v1 surface (remember/recall/improve/forget) + the session API
#     (cognee.api.v1.session.session: add_feedback, get_session, distill_session)
#     all import. (That venv was built from c505f326, which already carries the
#     session code; ba35b2fd is its #3107-merge descendant — either installs the
#     same working session API, so the pin is upgraded to the unambiguous one.)
#   - There is no published PyPI release carrying this yet; install from git.
#
# ⚠ Day-1 smoke test (the "Lessons" counter depends on this): confirm glm-4.7-flash can emit the
#   strict JSON cognify/distill_session need. Small local models often can't. If it fails, point
#   Cognee's LLM at a bigger/hosted model (site-building stays on Codex; A/B fairness unaffected).
